National Bank of Greece SA
 


overview

Deposit Guarantee
Bank Identifiers
Locations



  


















Established in 1841, National Bank of Greece is one of the largest financial groups 
in Greece, with a strong presence in Southeast Europe and Eastern Mediterranean. 
National Bank of Greece is a universal bank providing a broad range of products 
and services in the areas of retail, private, corporate and investment banking. National Bank of Greece SA operates as a branch of National Bank of Greece, S.A. (Greece).  National Bank of Greece SA participates in deposit guarantee scheme of the United Kingdom. 
This scheme covers accounts up to 85 000 GBP per bank per depositor.  National Bank of Greece SA is located in London.




